 take pictures with the cameras of our cell phones, send them to others and display them on the internet. We like to frequently communicate by photographic means in social networks, comment on them and evaluate them. New practices of the production, use and arrangement of pictures that question traditional ideas of authorship, reception and truth have been established. This volume is the first book that systematically introduces the new technologies and cultural practices used to distribute images and make them effective.  afunded by Brandenburgischen Zentrums für Medienwissenschaften (ZeM)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aAutorschaft. 4aBild. 4aBildwissenschaft. 4aDigitale Kultur. 4aDigitale Medien. 4aInternet. 4aMedienwissenschaft. 4aNetzwerkgesellschaft. 4aRezeption. 4aSocial Media. 4aSoziale Medien. 4aVisuelle Kultur. 4aWahrheit. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aAuthorship.  aDigital Culture.  aDigital Media.  aImage.  aInternet.  aMedia Studies.  aNetwork Society.  aPerception.  aSocial Media.  aTruth.  aVisual Culture.  aVisual Studies.1 aHolschbach, Susanne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLöffler, Petra, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut2 aBrandenburgischen Zentrums für Medienwissenschaften (ZeM)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2018z9783110602999oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839440704zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/978383944070442